<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: 'Transform' property with 'rotateY' function</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-3d-transforms/#transform-functions" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The 'transform' property with 'rotateY' function is supported." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #idcontainer
            {
                left: 100px;
                position: absolute;
                top: 100px;
            }
            #idchild1
            {
                background-color: yellow;
                height: 100px;
                position: absolute;
                transform: perspective(20px) rotateY(10deg);
                width: 100px;
            }
        </style>
            
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the yellow square with 'Filler Text' appears to be rotated backwards counter-clockwise.</p>
        <div id="idcontainer">
            <div id="idchild1">
                Filler Text<br/>
                Filler Text<br/>
                Filler Text<br/>
                Filler Text<br/>
                Filler Text<br/>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
